@startuml Energy Grid Customer Load

!include energy-grid-substation.puml

' A collection of equipment at one common system voltage forming a switchgear.
' The equipment typically consists of breakers, busbars, instrumentation, control, regulation and protection devices as well as assemblies of all these.
entity VoltageLevel <<context>> extends EquipmentContainer {
    ' highVoltageLimit: float /' The bus bar's high voltage limit.\nThe limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with lowVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present. '/
    ' lowVoltageLimit: float /' The bus bar's low voltage limit.\nThe limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with highVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present. '/
}

' An EnergyConsumer is a generic user of energy - a  point of consumption on the power system model. 
' According to IEC 61968-13, a MV  customer is a **CustomerLoad** and a LV customer is an **EquivalentLoad**.
'
' <<key>> decision:
' - **`CustomerLoad`** — MV background load contributing to transformer stress. Its `p` (active power) is part of the total load
'   the transformer must carry before any EV charging is added. The agent must sum all CustomerLoad.p values under a
'   transformer to correctly compute available headroom: headroom = ratedS − (ΣCustomerLoad.p + ΣEquivalentLoad.p + ΣUsagePoint.estimatedLoad).
'   Without it, the agent risks overloading a transformer that is already near capacity from MV commercial/industrial customers.
entity CustomerLoad <<key>> {
    customerLoadName: string /' The name of the customer load. '/
    p: float /' Active power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node. For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage. Starting value for a steady state solution. Default: 0.0 '/
    ' pfixed: float /' Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node. Default: 0.0 '/
    ' q: float /' Reactive power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node. For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage. Starting value for a steady state solution. Default: 0.0 '/
    ' qfixed: float /' Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node. Default: 0.0 '/
    ' powerFactor: float /' the power factor value '/
}

VoltageLevel --> Substation : MemberOf_Substation /' Shows a relationship to a substation '/

CustomerLoad --> VoltageLevel : MemberOf_EquipmentContainerVL /' A CustomerLoad can be assciated to an equipment container via the same voltage level. '/

@enduml
